<header class="header">
  <h1>Best Seed Company for Cool Climate Vegetables</h1>
  <p class="tagline">
    In cooler climates, reliability matters more than variety.
  </p>
  <p class="lede">
    <strong>For most gardeners, West Coast Seeds and High Mowing Organic Seeds are the best choices for cool climate vegetables because they offer varieties that perform reliably with limited heat. Johnny’s Selected Seeds is a strong option when you want more control over maturity and crop selection.</strong>
  </p>
  <p>
    Cool climate gardening is less forgiving than it looks. Lower temperatures, slower growth, and shorter windows all reduce the margin for error.
  </p>
  <p>
    That makes seed selection more important than usual.
  </p>
</header>

