<section class="guideSection">
  <h2>What Actually Matters in Cool Climate Gardening</h2>

  <p>
    <strong>Cold tolerance.</strong> Some crops continue growing in cooler temperatures while others stall.
  </p>

  <p>
    <strong>Shorter maturity time.</strong> Crops need to finish within a limited window.
  </p>

  <p>
    <strong>Reliable performance.</strong> Consistency matters more than peak yield potential.
  </p>

  <p>
    These factors determine whether a crop will reach harvest, not just whether it germinates.
  </p>
</section>

<section class="guideSection">
  <h2>Why Cool Climate Gardens Struggle</h2>

  <p>
    The biggest challenge is not starting crops, but finishing them.
  </p>

  <p>
    Common issues include:
  </p>

  <ul class="plainList">
    <li>slow growth during cooler periods</li>
    <li>crops stalling instead of maturing</li>
    <li>harvest windows closing before crops are ready</li>
  </ul>

  <p>
    These problems often appear later in the season, when there is less time to adjust.
  </p>

  <p>
    That is why it helps to understand <a href="/guides/will-my-crop-mature-before-first-frost/">whether crops will mature before the first frost</a> so you can choose varieties that actually fit your timeline.
  </p>
</section>

