<section class="guideSection">
  <h2>What Most People Get Wrong</h2>

  <p>
    <strong>They choose varieties suited to warmer climates.</strong> Not all crops perform well without sustained heat.
  </p>

  <p>
    <strong>They ignore maturity timing.</strong> Slower crops are more likely to struggle or fail to finish.
  </p>

  <p>
    <strong>They assume all seeds perform similarly.</strong> Small differences in variety selection can have a large impact.
  </p>
</section>

